race.comment: ZAMBADA ICON (7) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fifth (24.88) last time in a Grade 5 at Bendigo. Solid record at the distance winning three races. Has ability and looks hard to stop. RED CABANG (8) was unfancied last time out but hit the ground running to lead all the way, scoring by one length (26.05) at Ballarat in a T3 RSTW over 450m. Has never been out of the placings from two starts out of this box. Capable of going well again. ROWDY'S BEAST (3) prominent throughout and boxed on soundly to finish in the minors when second (25.97) at Warrnambool in Grade 4/5. Missed the frame only look here. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Will give a great sight again. COUNTY KILDARE (2) cannot be underestimated.
